\subsection{BMS-supertranslations of the Schwarzschild metric on   ${\mathscr I}^-$ }

Taking the limit $r_S \to \infty$ takes the future horizon $r=r_S$ to past null infinity $\mathscr{I}^-.$ Therefore, taking this limit in \eqref{Supertranslationen} 
yields the BMS-supertranslations at null infinity $\mathscr{I}^-$ with respect to the particular coordinate conditions used in the previous section:

text:
\begin{align}
\delta_{\zeta_f} g_{\mu \nu}
=
\begin{pmatrix}
0 & 0 & -(1-\frac{r_S}{r})\frac{\partial f}{\partial {\vartheta}} & -(1-\frac{r_S}{r})\frac{\partial f}{\partial {\varphi}}\\
0 & 0 & 0 & 0\\
* & * & 2r^2(\frac{1}{r}-\frac{1}{r_S})\frac{\partial^2 f}{\partial {\vartheta}^2} & 2r^2(\frac{1}{r}-\frac{1}{r_S})(\frac{\partial^2 f}{\partial {\vartheta} \partial {\varphi}}-\cot {\vartheta} \frac{\partial f}{\partial {\varphi}})\\
* & * & * & 2r^2(\frac{1}{r}-\frac{1}{r_S})(\frac{\partial^2 f}{\partial  {\varphi}^2} + \sin {\vartheta} \cos {\vartheta} \frac{\partial f}{\partial {\vartheta}})
\end{pmatrix}
.
\label{Bogoliubov}
\end{align}

\begin{align}
\delta_{\eta_g} g_{\mu \nu}=
\begin{pmatrix}
0 & 0 & -(1-\frac{r_S}{r})\frac{\partial g}{\partial {\vartheta}} & -(1-\frac{r_S}{r})\frac{\partial g}{\partial {\varphi}}\\
0 & 0 & 0 & 0\\
* & * & 2r \frac{\partial^2 g}{\partial {\vartheta}^2} & 2r (\frac{\partial^2 g}{\partial {\vartheta} \partial {\varphi}}-\cot {\vartheta} \frac{\partial g}{\partial {\varphi}})\\
* & * & * & 2r (\frac{\partial^2 g}{\partial  {\varphi}^2} + \sin {\vartheta} \cos {\vartheta} \frac{\partial g}{\partial {\vartheta}})
\end{pmatrix}\, .
\label{BMS-Bogoliubov}
\end{align}

